               <msContents>
                  <summary>In Minasian collection, the generic title of Akhlāq [Ethics] is given to a number of brief treatises that have defective incipits and explicits, hence lacking title and author information. They all, however, have the genral topic of ethics in common.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="WadhMinasian_704-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <note type="content-genre">Ethics</note>
                     <author key="person_f407" role="aut" change="#role-assignment">
                        <persName xml:lang="en">Anonymous</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_2969">[Akhlāq]</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_2969">[اخلاق]</title>
                     <note xml:lang="en"/>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa" defective="true">بسمله، و اولو الارحام بعضهم اولی ببعض. شارع مقدس نظر به اختلاف نسبتی که در اقربا و ذوی الاقربا مثبت می‌باشد…</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa" defective="true">… مسلم و کافر و یهود و نصاری در آن مجلس عام از آن معجزه خبردار شدند…</explicit>
                     <listBibl>
                        <head>Sequence Number in the Persian Catalogue:</head><bibl>FAW 27</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                  </msItem>
